qas.question: Who occupied the role that would later become prime minister under Henry VIII?
Who held the equivalent of the post of prime minister under Queen Anne?
Who served as the head minister under Charles II?
Who did the monarchs of England and the United Kingdom not trust?
What position did Thomas Cromwell hold under Queen Anne?

context: The monarchs of England and the United Kingdom had <b3_0>ministers<b3_0/> in whom they placed special trust and who were regarded as the head of the government. Examples were <a0_0>Thomas Cromwell<a0_0/> under Henry VIII; William Cecil, Lord Burghley under Elizabeth I; <a2_0>Clarendon<a2_0/> under Charles II and <a1_0>Godolphin<a1_0/> under Queen Anne. These ministers held a variety of formal posts, but were commonly known as "the minister", the "chief minister", the "first minister" and finally the "<b4_0>prime minister<b4_0/>".
